<H3> <TI>   `National Assembly' Meets, Appoints Officers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `National Assembly' Meets, Appoints Officers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0606140694 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 0330 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0606140694 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 0330 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The National Assembly Presidium held a [word 
indistinct] meeting this morning under the chairmanship of 
Speaker Anis Hasan Yahya. During this meeting, the assembly 
discussed a number of topics on its agenda and made the 
necessary decisions. The presidium endorsed the distribution of 
duties among its members as follows: 
  (?Sha'fil 'Umar Ali), deputy assembly speaker for 
parliamentary affairs and foreign liaison; 
  Ahmad Ubayd Bin Daghr, deputy assembly speaker for 
organizational and technical affairs; 
  'Abd-al-Qawi Muhammad Rashad, deputy assembly speaker for 
permanent committees' affairs; 
  'Abd-al-Rahman Asim, deputy assembly speaker for the affairs 
of the government apparatus and the public and mixed sectors. 
  The presidium also endorsed the appointment of Brother Taha 
'Abdallah Muhammad as secretary general of the National Assembly 
Presidium. 

</TEXT>

