<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Buwayz Denies Secret Negotiations With Israel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Buwayz Denies Secret Negotiations With Israel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0306113294 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 3 Jun 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> PM0306113294 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Faris Buwayz' Statement to AL-SHARQ </F>
AL-AWSAT: Beirut Denies Existence of Secret Negotiations With 
Tel Aviv, Stresses No Plan To Evacuate Palestinians"] 
  [Excerpt] Amman, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT--Lebanese Foreign 
Minister Faris Buwayz has denied that there are any secret 
negotiations between Lebanon and Israel like those held between 
the Palestinians and the Israelis in Oslo. He said that the 
negotiations held between us are those conducted in the 
framework of the declared peace negotiations with the other Arab 
delegations. 
  Answering a question put to him by AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT during 
his visit to Jordan, he said: We have not received any Israeli 
plans regarding withdrawal from southern Lebanon, neither 
through U.S. diplomacy nor any other quarters. 
  He added that the Lebanese position has always been clear 
since the Madrid conference, as we refused to sit with the 
Israelis or to discuss any partial solution. Nor did we accept 
anything except full withdrawal from Lebanese territory. 
  He stressed that Israel is trying, by means of unclear 
plans, 
to dissolve Resolution 425, which stipulates full withdrawal 
from Lebanese territory. We are calling for the implementation 
of all the UN resolutions, including Resolution 425 concerning 
Lebanon. Buwayz also stressed the need to continue and intensify 
coordination among the Arab parties concerned with the peace 
negotiations, as he regards it as support for the positions of 
the delegations participating in the peace negotiations. 
  On the Palestinian self-rule agreement Buwayz said: What the 
Palestinians brothers have arrived at with the Israelis 
regarding "Gaza-Jericho" is an achievement -- which reflects 
positively on the other negotiation tracks and opens the door to 
progress on the other tracks. 
  Buwayz warned of Israel's intentions in trying to divide 
solutions and single out the Arab parties individually in order 
to impose Israel's will and ambitions on the Arab states. It is 
always trying -- through trial balloons -- to agree a solution 
with this or that party regarding such and such. All these 
things are trial balloons for all the Arab tracks. 
  Buwayz denied that his country has any plan to evacuate 
400,000 Palestinians who have been living in Lebanon for several 
years and who hold Lebanese travel documents. He said: All the 
rumors in this connection are untrue, and we are not at all 
thinking of evacuating our Palestinian brothers. But we support 
their right to return to their land and recover their legitimate 
rights. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

