<H3> <TI>   Nasrallah: Resistance Against Israelis To Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nasrallah: Resistance Against Israelis To Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0306115794 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1030 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0306115794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] After taking part in the funeral of the martyrs 
of the Israeli raid at Rawdat al-Shahidayn Mosque at 1100 today, 
Hizballah Secretary General Hasan Nasrallah stressed that the 
confrontation with the enemy will continue until the land is 
liberated. He called for withdrawing from negotiations with the 
enemy and for not relying on the UN Security Council. He called 
for making the resistance a general national plan. He said that 
the resistance is the rock on which the occupation will founder 
and the homeland will be unified. He declared that the 
resistance has been born anew with the fall of the martyrs 
yesterday. He stressed that any peace given to the killers of 
prophets and people and the usurpers of land and sanctities is a 
disgrace no matter what the justifications and circumstances. 
[passage omitted] 

