<H3> <TI>   Israeli Tank, Artillery Reinforcements Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israeli Tank, Artillery Reinforcements Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0306171794 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1530 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0306171794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A state of top alert prevails among the Israeli 
occupation forces and their puppet militia, on one side, and the 
Lebanese Army and the Lebanese resistance groups, on the other. 
  The NATIONAL NEWS AGENCY has learned that the UN Interim 
Force in Lebanon has placed the personnel manning its 
checkpoints on alert. It also beefed up the checkpoints with 
additional troops. 
  The occupation forces have mobilized additional troops 
inside 
the occupied border strip. Convoys of tanks, military vehicles, 
and troop carriers have been deployed on the hills overlooking 
the liberated areas near the international border. 
  According to security sources, the Israeli occupation forces 
have deployed long-range mobile artillery on the Muhaybib and 
al-'Abbad hills, and Jabal Humayd. 
  AFP reported today that large numbers of Israeli tanks, 
armored vehicles, artillery pieces, and troops carriers were 
deployed on the Lebanese-Israeli international border but did 
not cross. 
  Meanwhile, contrary to some media's claims, no flood of 
refugees has been reported from the areas under attack despite 
the atmosphere of tension there. 

</TEXT>

