<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A state of extreme caution prevails in various 
areas in the south and western al-Biqa'. The occupation forces 
last night machine-gunned the Habbush valley and al-Wadi 
al-Akhdar from their position in al-Suwayda'. They directed 
sniper fire at the Habbush road. 
  Israeli helicopters flew over al-Tayyibah and al-Qantarah at 
2315 yesterday. Helicopters also flew over the villages of the 
western sector and the plain south of Tyre after midnight last 
night, dropping flares over these areas. 
  Enemy aircraft were seen over Tyre at 1200 today. 
  Security sources in southern Lebanon have reported that the 
occupation forces brought into the occupied border strip tanks, 
armored personnel carriers, and long-range artillery and 
deployed them on the hills overlooking the areas adjacent to the 
occupied part of the south. 

