<H3> <TI>   PRC Vice Foreign Minister Arrives, Makes Statement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PRC Vice Foreign Minister Arrives, Makes Statement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0306143394 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1115 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0306143394 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] PRC Vice Foreign Minister Tian Zengpei arrived in 
Damascus today on a visit to Syria that will last for several 
days. He was received at Damascus International Airport by 
Rislan 'Allush, the assistant foreign minister, a number of 
Foreign Ministry officials, and the PRC ambassador in Damascus 
and embassy staff. 
  In a statement to the SANA correspondent, Tian Zengpei 
expressed his extreme happiness at visiting Syria and said: 
China and Syria are two friendly countries whose peoples are 
tied by traditional friendship. Over the past 38 years of 
diplomatic relations between our two countries, our friendship 
and cooperation witnessed satisfactory progress based on the 
five principles of peaceful coexistence. Our two countries 
continued to exchange sympathy and support on the international 
arena, holding close or identical views on many important 
international issues. 
  The Chinese official said: Increasing visits and 
consultations between our two countries in this age, which is 
characterized by a changing international climate, assumes great 
importance for increasing understanding and strengthening 
friendship. I am looking forward to meeting with the Syrian 
officials concerned to exchange views on international and 
regional issues of common concern and to look for ways of 
developing bilateral relations. I will witness the great 
achievements realized by the Syrian people under the leadership 
of President Hafiz al-Asad in the field of expanding national 
production and developing the country. 
  Concluding his statement, Tian Zengpei said: I am certain 
that this visit of mine will contribute toward further 
increasing and strengthening ties of cooperation and friendship 
between our two countries. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

