<H4>    Second Prithvi Test Successful </H4>

<F P=102> BK0606124094 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1230 
GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0606124094 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The second use trial of the short-range 
surface-to-surface missile Prithvi was successfully conducted at 
the interim test range in Orissa today. The Defense Ministry 
sources in New Delhi said that the launch was to the maximum 
range of the missile and all the mission requirements were 
achieved. Today's test flight of the sleek missile is the 14th 
in the series, and second from the indigenously built [word 
indistinct] mobile launcher. 
  The prime minister, Mr. P.V. Narasimha Rao, has complimented 
the Army, the scientists, and staff of the concerned 
organizations for the accomplishment. 

</TEXT>

