<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Kuwait </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister: GCC To Define Stance on Yemen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister: GCC To Define Stance on Yemen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0206100094 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 2 Jun 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> PM0206100094 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Sawsan Abu-Husayn: "Sabah al-Ahmad Tells </F>
AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT: Final Gulf Position on Yemen To Be Defined 
Next Week"] 
  [Text] Cairo -- Kuwaiti Foreign Minister Shaykh Sabah 
al-Ahmad has said in a statement to AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT that the 
Gulf Cooperation Council [GCC] foreign ministers' meeting 
scheduled to be held in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia next week 
will define the final position on the Yemeni war, especially as 
the Gulf states have monitored the position of both the north 
and the south and the contacts made between the two sides, and 
in view of the adoption of the Security Council resolution. He 
stressed that all efforts should be aimed first at securing a 
cease-fire. 
  Asked about the possibility of restoring Kuwaiti-Iraqi 
relations if Iraqi President Saddam Husayn announces in a clear 
statement that Kuwait is a free independent state which Iraqi 
has nothing to do with, the Kuwaiti foreign minister said: The 
Iraqi president must announce that and register this recognition 
in the Security Council and the United Nations first. Because 
there are no relations between the two countries at the 
bilateral level. And there are Security Council resolutions 
which Iraq must comply with and implement first. On lifting the 
embargo in Iraq and the Security Council's remarks in this 
connection, he said: We have nothing to do with that issue, and 
the council must decide what it deems right in accordance with 
the resolution adopted by it. On Arab reconciliation he said 
that it still needs time, especially in view of the current 
deteriorating Arab conditions, as the region is full of problems 
and disputes which should be resolved first. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

