<H3> <TI>   Missiles Reportedly Injure Worshipers in Aden Mosque </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Missiles Reportedly Injure Worshipers in Aden Mosque </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0206190594 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1500 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0206190594 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1500 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A responsible source at the Armed Forces Command has 
told the Yemeni news agency in Aden that a few hours after the 
issuance of the resolution of the UN Security Council calling 
for an immediate cease-fire, a development welcomed by our 
country which declared that it will fully observe all its points 
and will welcome the dispatch of the investigating committee 
formed for this purpose, the forces of the ruling military 
regime in Sanaa today launched a number of surface-to-surface 
missiles on the capital, Aden. These missiles were intercepted 
by our air defenses. Fragments of one of the missiles fell on 
one of Aden's mosques where worshipers were engaged in dawn 
prayers. A number of them were seriously injured and were 
subsequently taken to the hospital for treatment. Later a 
number of Arab, foreign, and local correspondents gathered at 
the scene as eyewitnesses to this [word indistinct] incident. 

</TEXT>

