<H3> <TI>   Northern Troops Said To Bomb Palestinian Camp </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Northern Troops Said To Bomb Palestinian Camp </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0206151894 Paris AFP in English 1503 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0206151894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, June 2 (AFP) -- Northern Yemeni troops fired 
missiles and artillery shells at a Palestinian camp on Thursday 
[2 June] in Dar Sa'd, north of the southern stronghold Aden, 
Palestinian sources said here. 
  Thirty Palestinian families were evacuated from the camp to 
Aden, the sources said, but it was not known whether anybody was 
killed or injured in the attack. 
  Several Palestinian camps are situated in Yemen. The attack 
came as gun battles raged around Aden on Thursday despite a UN 
resolution Wednesday for a cease-fire in the civil war which 
broke out on May 5. 
  At least six civilians were injured during northern air 
raids 
on Aden Thursday, a southern military source said. 

</TEXT>

