<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Expresses Appreciates for UN Resolution </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet Expresses Appreciates for UN Resolution </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0206122694 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0206122694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Council of Ministers held an extraordinary 
meeting this morning under the chairmanship of Acting Prime 
Minister Dr. Muhammad Sa'id al-'Attar to discuss Security 
Council Resolution 924 adopted in its session No. 3,386, which 
was held on 1 June. 
  After discussing the resolution, the council expressed its 
appreciation for the resolution based on the provisions of the 
UN Charter, particularly the Republic of Yemen's sovereignty, 
independence, and territorial integrity. 
  The council will resume its meeting this evening. 

