<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement issued by the Council of Ministers; place and </F>
date not given] 
  [Text] The government of the Republic of Yemen has taken 
cognizance of UN Security Council Resolution 924 of 1 June 1994 
passed on the situation in the Republic of Yemen. 
  While expressing its appreciation of the wording of the 
resolution, which addressed the situation in our country from 
the perspective of the national unity and constitutional 
legitimacy of the Republic of Yemen, and in accordance with the 
firm principles enshrined in the UN Charter, chief among which 
were the principles pertaining to national sovereignty, 
territorial integrity, and noninterference in domestic affairs 
-- something that would lead to an end to the bloodshed and to 
the start of a (?dialogue) to resolve internal disputes through 
peaceful means and reestablish peace and stability in our 
country --, the government of the Republic of Yemen reiterates 
its willingness to deal with the resolution in a positive 
spirit, and in a manner that would result in its implementation 
in an integrated manner by all concerned parties. 

</TEXT>

