<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Source' Reacts to `Secessionist' Aden Government </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Source' Reacts to `Secessionist' Aden Government </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0306053594 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0306053594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A responsible source has reacted to the 
secessionist rebels' step to form a secessionist government in 
Aden. He said: This secessionist act, which ignores 
constitutional legitimacy, aims only to obstruct the efforts 
exerted to achieve security and stability in our country in 
light of UN Security Council Resolution 924. 
  The source added: The step taken by the secessionists, who 
have rebelled against constitutional legitimacy, reminds us of 
another step taken by the secessionist gang, which rebelled 
against legitimacy and democracy when the three-day cease-fire 
decision was issued on 21 May 1994 in response to a desire 
expressed by the custodian of the two holy places, King Fahd 
Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz of fraternal Saudi Arabia. Then, 'Ali Salim 
al-Bid shocked the world by announcing the secession despite his 
knowledge of the good efforts exerted by the custodian of the 
two holy places in the hope that his desire, to which our 
political leadership responded favorably, would be a prelude to 
a permanent cessation of fighting and a solution to the disputes 
through constructive dialogue. 
  The source added that this secessionist gang has confirmed 
once again that it insists on shedding the blood of the Yemeni 
people in order to impose secession through force of arms. 
  The source concluded by saying: The government of the 
Republic of Yemen considers this illegitimate step a blatant 
challenge to the UN Security Council and a flagrant violation of 
Resolution 924. Despite this fact, this flagrant violation of 
the UN Security Council will not deter the government of the 
Republic of Yemen from dealing with that resolution in a 
positive spirit and in manner that will lead to implementing it 
in a comprehensive way by all those concerned. 

</TEXT>

