<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
chairman of the Presidential Council, and President Francois 
Mitterrand of the friendly French Republic, spoke on the 
telephone last night. 
  The two leaders discussed relations between the two friendly 
countries and ways of promoting them to serve common interests. 
They discussed developments in Yemen after some secessionist, 
rebellious elements within the Socialist Party ignited a war as 
a means to achieve their objectives. 
  The brother chairman of the Presidential Council briefed the 
French president about the reality of what is happening in our 
country and the brave confrontation of the secessionist rebels 
to champion unity, democracy, and constitutional legitimacy. 
  The brother chairman of the Presidential Council expressed 
his extreme appreciation for the position of the French 
president and France in support of unity, democracy, and party 
pluralism in our country. 
  The French president reiterated his country's support for 
Yemeni unity, democratic approach, and development drive. 

