<H3> <TI>   Al-Ainsi, Chinese Charge Discuss Developments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Ainsi, Chinese Charge Discuss Developments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2905130194 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 29 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2905130194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Deputy Prime Minister 'Abd-al-Wahhab al-Anisi this 
morning received (Chan Chichan), the charge d'affaires at the 
embassy of the People's Republic of China in our country. 
  They discussed developments in the Yemeni arena and ties 
between the two friendly countries. 
  During the meeting, the Chinese charge d'affaires underlined 
his country's concern for Yemeni unity since it is a factor of 
stability in the region. 
  For his part, the brother deputy prime minister voiced 
appreciation for China's position on the events and developments 
in our region. He also expressed the hope that the ties of 
cooperation between the two countries will improve for the 
benefit of the two friendly peoples' mutual interests. 
  The meeting also touched on the discussions that will be 
held 
at the UN Security Council and our country's position, since 
these discussions run counter to the UN charter and constitute a 
precedent that will affect not only Yemen, but also other 
countries with worse internal situations than those in Yemen. 

</TEXT>

