<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   *Shahid-e Hashemi-Nezhad Refinery Volume Up </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    *Shahid-e Hashemi-Nezhad Refinery Volume Up </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94LA0168G Tehran KEYHAN-E HAVA'I in Persian 11 May 94 p 11 </F>
<F P=103> 94LA0168G </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran KEYHAN-E HAVA'I </F>
<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

  [Text] Tehran, 13 Ordibehesht [3 May] -- The capacity of 
Shahid-e Hashemi-Nezhad Refinery will increase to 35 million 
cubic meters [m[.sup]3[/]] per day. 
  Engineer Hoseyn Bashiri, chief of the Shahid-e 
Hashemi-Nezhad 
Gas Refinery, announced the above at a press conference. He 
said: During the Second Five-Year Plan two new units will be 
added to the refinery's three existing units and the refinery's 
nominal capacity will increase from 21 million m[.sup]3[/] 
per day to 35 million m[.sup]3[/]. 
  Engineer Bashiri said: The gas from this refinery supplies 
the three great provinces of Khorasan, Semnan, and Mazandaran 
and it provides fuel for five power plants at Neka, Tus, 
Shari'ati, Shirvan, and Mashhad. 
  He said: In the First Five-Year Plan two units were 
established at the power plant in the Gonbadli region, where we 
share gas fields with Turkmenistan. One of these two units has 
now been put into operation, and it produces 2.5 million 
m[.sup]3[/] of cubic sweet gas. The second unit is also about 
to go into operation. 
  It is necessary to note that the Shahid-e Hashemi Gas 
Refinery, which is considered one of the largest gas refineries 
of its kind, is 35 km from Sarakhs and 165 km from Mashhad, in 
the northeast part of the province of Khorasan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

