<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   *Trade Attaches To Be Stationed in Embassies </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    *Trade Attaches To Be Stationed in Embassies </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94LA0166G Tehran KEYHAN-E HAVA'I in Persian 20 Apr 94 p 10 </F>
<F P=103> 94LA0166G </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran KEYHAN-E HAVA'I </F>
<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

  [Text] Tehran, 23 Farvardin [12 April] KEYHAN-E HAVA'I News 
Service -- To do marketing and create facilities to develop 
nonoil exports, trade attaches will soon be stationed at all the 
Islamic Republic of Iran's embassies, with the cooperation of 
the Foreign Ministry. 
  Engineer 'Ali Sa'idlu, deputy minister of commerce for trade 
and chief of the Iran Export Development Center, announced the 
above at a gathering of news reporters. He said: In this regard 
talks have been held with Foreign Ministry officials, because 
trade attaches in the embassies will help develop exports. 
  He discussed the provisions the government has made to 
support exporters of nonoil goods. He said: Based on a measure 
enacted by the Money and Credit Council, the share of credits to 
be provided for exports is increased from last year's 
6.5-percent figure to 8.5 percent for the current year, with a 
commission rate of 18 percent. 
  Engineer Sa'idlu also added: The Supreme Exports Council, 
which met recently chaired by President of the Republic Hojjat 
ol-Eslam val-Moslemin Hashemi-Rafsanjani and attended by a 
number of ministers working in economic affairs, will soon 
prepare a comprehensive export program. 
  He explained that the measures enacted by this council, 
along 
with the new activities of the exports guarantee fund, will 
solve the problems in the export sector. 
  Engineer Sa'idlu noted that imports of goods must be done in 
exchange for exports. On this same basis, the Export Development 
Center sets prices on export goods and gives an affidavit to 
that effect to the exporters. Using these affidavits it is 
possible to import the goods needed by the country. 
  In conclusion, he said that holding an international 
exposition all over the country depends on obtaining 
authorization from the Export Development Center. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

