<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Chairman' Swears In National Assembly Members </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Chairman' Swears In National Assembly Members </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0206193594 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in English 1600 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0206193594 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in English 1600 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The National Assembly of the Democratic Republic of 
Yemen [DRY] held a session this morning under the chairmanship 
of Mr. Anis Hasan Yahya, the chairman of the assembly. The 
session began with the national anthem and a recitation from the 
holy Koran and a minute's pause to mourn the martyrs. At the 
beginning of the session, the members of the National Assembly 
were sworn in and then the presidium of the assembly was elected 
of four members as follows: Sha'fil Umar 'Ali, Ahmad Ubayd Bin 
Daghr, 'Abd-al-Qawi Muhammad Rashad, and 'Abd-al-Rahim Asim. 
Mr. Anis Hasan Yahya was elected as speaker of the assembly. 
The members of the assembly decided to change the name of the 
provisional assembly into the National Assembly in order to 
facilitate dealings between it and the state institutions. The 
National Assembly discussed with vitality the tasks designated 
to it. It was decided that the assembly continue its sessions 
in order to review the remaining topics of its agenda after the 
assembly had decided that it is in a state of permanent session. 
The attendances [as heard] greeted the big role played by the 
sons of the DRY to repel the Sanaa rulers' forces, which 
continued aggression. They praised the role of the Security 
Council and the positive role played by the Arab countries to 
stop bloodshed. 

</TEXT>

