<F P=102>   LD0206145894 Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1300 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0206145894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At Carthage Palace this morning President Zine El 
Abidine Ben Ali and Foreign Minister Habib Ben Yahia received a 
delegation from the U.S. Senate which included Paul Simon, Harry 
Reid, and Russell Feingold. 
  Following the meeting, which was also attended by U.S. 
Ambassador John McCarthy, Paul Simon said that during the 
meeting he and the accompanying delegation expressed their 
extreme appreciation to his excellency the head of state and 
their great admiration for Tunisia. 
  He pointed out that the talks dealt in particular with 
issues 
which were of concern to the region and the peace process in the 
Middle East. 
  In this respect, he said we are very keen to express our 
thanks to President Zine El Abidine Ben Ali and the Tunisian 
people for the efforts exerted by Tunisia and its president at 
the United Nations for the benefit of the peace process in the 
Middle East. 

