today that the UN secretary-general had a conception which was 
compatible with Moroccan interests on settling the Saharan issue. 
  The Saharan official said that the criteria for determining 
the voters' identity, introduced by the former UN 
secretary-general, Peres de Cuellar, two days before his term in 
office came to an end, were reducing the hope of finding a just 
and fair solution to the issue. [end recording] 

