<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Additional Katyusha Volleys Fired at Galilee </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0206193994 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1930 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0206193994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An additional Katyusha volley was fired at the 
western Galilee a short time ago. Menahem Horowitz, our 
correspondent in the north, updates us: 
  [Horowitz] Good evening, about half an hour ago, explosions 
were heard once again in the western Galilee. Katyushas were 
fired from Lebanon at the Galilee and the security zone in south 
Lebanon. In response, IDF [Israel Defense Forces] and SLA [South 
Lebanese Army] artillery fired at terrorist positions in south 
Lebanon. IDF guns have shelled terrorist targets there 
intermittently throughout the day. Many northern border 
inhabitants are spending the night in shelters and are 
anticipating a very tense night. 

</TEXT>

