<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Kuwait </F>
<H3> <TI>   5 Iraqis, 1 National Get Death Sentence in Bush Case </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    5 Iraqis, 1 National Get Death Sentence in Bush Case </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    No `Political Intervention' Said in Decision </H4>

<F P=102> LD0406120494 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 1054 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0406120494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Kuwait, 4 Jun -- Councillor Salah al-Fahd, 
president of the State Security Court, stressed that sentences, 
which the court had passed, were not influenced by any political 
interventions from any quarter, pointing out that the defendants 
were recruited by Iraqi intelligence service to assassinate 
former President Bush and to carry out acts infringing on 
security [words indistinct] [passage omitted] 
  The court also passed a death sentence on a Kuwaiti citizen, 
Badr Jiyad Thamir Mutlaq al-Shammari and fined the first four 
defendants a sum of 3,000 Kuwait dinars and a collective custom 
penalty of 1,500 Kuwait dinars for the first five and the 11th 
defendants. 
  The State Security Court witnessed a fist fight in the dock 
between the first defendant Ra'd al-Asadi and the 11th 
defendant, Badr Jiyad al-Shammari following the issuing of 
sentences as the defendant al-Shammari claimed that Al-Asadi had 
implicated him in the case. 

</TEXT>

