<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Council of Ministers Passes Draft Laws </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206122294 Nouakchott ORTM Radio in Arabic 2200 GMT 1 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0206122294 </F>
<F P=104>  Nouakchott ORTM Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Council of Ministers met today, Wednesday, 1 
June 1994, under the chairmanship of His Eminence Mr. Maaouiya 
Ould Sid' Ahmed Taya, the president of the Republic. The 
council studied and approved the following draft laws: 
  1. A draft law that allows the ratification of the loan 
agreement signed on 26 April 1994 between the Islamic Republic 
of Mauritania and the international development association 
regarding the financing of the agricultural services project. 
[passage omitted] 
  2. A draft law that includes the amendment of Law No. 91-24, 
issued on 25 June 1991, regarding political parties. This draft 
law aims to simplify and extend the criteria used for the 
distribution of financial aid put aside by the government for 
national political parties. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

