<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Shar' Comments on Israeli Attacks, Peace Process </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Shar' Comments on Israeli Attacks, Peace Process </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0306132294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1110 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0306132294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 3 Jun (MENA)--Syrian Foreign Minister Faruq 
al- Shar' affirmed today that Israel's latest aggression against 
south Lebanon yesterday is clear evidence that Israel does not 
desire peace and places obstacles to the peace efforts to cause 
tension in the region. 
  In press statements made here today, he said the lack of 
progress in the peace process is being blamed on Israel, which 
does not want to withdraw from the Arab territories it occupied 
in 1967. 
  He said that the Arab parties are committed to the peace 
process and the UN Security Council resolutions. 
  Answering a question on the effect of the Israeli stance on 
achieving progress on the Syrian track, he said that although 
Israel does not want peace, the United States will not abandon 
the peace process. 
  He said the Lebanese have the right to defend themselves 
against the Israeli occupation of south Lebanon to implement 
international legitimacy and Security Council resolutions. 
  On the Syrian presence in Lebanon, he said this presence is 
aimed at helping the Lebanese people in reconstruction efforts. 
  Commenting on the situation in Yemen, the Syrian foreign 
minister said his country is currently holding intense contacts 
to stop the ongoing fighting in Yemen and preserve Yemen's unity. 

</TEXT>

