<H3> <TI>   Government Affirms Support for Hizballah Resistance </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Affirms Support for Hizballah Resistance </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0606191994 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0606191994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lebanese President Ilyas al-Hirawi and Prime 
Minister Rafiq al-Hariri have made separate telephone calls to 
'Allamah Sayyid Muhammad Husayn Fadlallah. They discussed with 
him the recent Zionist assaults on the Ba'labakk area. 
  Al-Hariri sent Lebanese Minister of State for Finance Fu'ad 
Sinyurah to the headquarters of Hizballah's Consultative 
Council. Sinyurah, speaking for the Lebanese Government, 
affirmed that the government support for the resistance will 
continue until the occupied territories are liberated. 
  Sinyurah announced: We express our appreciation for 
Hizballah's martyrs who gave their lives to defend the homeland 
and confront Israeli arrogance. 
  Meanwhile, Lebanese Foreign Minister Faris Buwayz described 
the Zionists' recent brutal attacks on Ba'labakk as an attempt 
to damage Syrian-Lebanese relations. 
  Speaking to the newspaper AL-SAFIR, Buwayz said that Israel 
has lately been exerting pressure on the Lebanese Government to 
make it halt the resistance operations against the Zionists in 
south Lebanon. He pointed out, however, that the Lebanese 
Government believes that as long as the Zionists occupy parts of 
the Lebanese territory, resistance is the people's legitimate 
right. 
  The Lebanese foreign minister referred to the total backing 
that the Lebanese public and their various political factions 
are giving to the resistance movement. He accused the United 
Nations of weakness and inability to adopt firm resolutions to 
halt the Zionist attacks on Lebanon. 

</TEXT>

