<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   NAM Conference Issues Communique, Concludes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NAM Conference Issues Communique, Concludes </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Ministers Issue Resolution on Rwanda </H4>

<F P=102> NC0306133194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0825 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0306133194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 3 Jun (MENA) -- The 11th conference of the 
Nonaligned Movement's [NAM] foreign ministers currently being 
held in Cairo has issued a resolution on Rwanda, urging the UN 
Security Council to quickly take all the necessary measures to 
immediately end the massacres taking place in Rwanda and to 
effectively provide all the necessary means for the deployment 
of peace keeping forces there as soon as possible. 
  The resolution, passed at the conclusion of the foreign 
ministers meetings today, also urges the international community 
to respond to the peaceful and humanitarian efforts being made 
in Rwanda by providing the material and financial resources and 
extending all practical assistance to ensure the immediate 
containment of pollution and the dangers to public health and 
the environment resulting from the human massacres taking place 
in Rwanda. 
  The resolution expresses the NAM's support for a roundtable 
with the participation of all the parties to the conflict. It 
calls for drawing up an action plan for the reconstruction and 
rehabilitation of Rwanda. 
  The resolution appeals to the international community not to 
delay in supporting the good initiative by Kenyan President 
Daniel arap Moi, which calls for a minisummit of the countries 
bordering Rwanda to be held in Nairobi early next week to 
discuss this issue. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

