<H3> <TI>   NAM Conference Issues Communique, Concludes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NAM Conference Issues Communique, Concludes </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Committee on South Africa Dissolved </H4>

<F P=102> NC0306123594 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1114 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0306123594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 3 Jun (MENA) -- The Nonaligned Movement's 
[NAM] foreign ministers conference issued a resolution today 
ending the work of the NAM committee on South Africa and 
submitting a recommendation to this effect to the movement's 
countries and governments leaders for ratification. 
  The conference said in its final session that this 
resolution 
is based on the start of a new stage in the history of South 
Africa following the holding of the first democratic elections 
there and the formation of a nonracial government. 
  It noted that the resolution is in line with the report 
presented by Indonesia's special envoy Nanasutrisna [name as 
received], who chaired the NAM session and who called for ending 
the work of the committee in light of these developments. 

</TEXT>

