<H3> <TI>   Israel Rejects Border Discussion With Jordan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israel Rejects Border Discussion With Jordan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0506160994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1505 GMT 5 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0506160994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Washington correspondent Arye Golan] </F>
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] While Jordan insists on 
immediately discussing the demarcation of its international 
border with Israel and border amendments in the 'Arava, Israel 
says that such a discussion can be held only in the framework of 
peace agreement negotiations. 
  What the parties do intend to discuss is the Jordanian 
grievance aired over the past few days that the 
Israeli-Palestinian economic agreement signed in Paris has 
driven Jordan out of the West Bank. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

