<H3> <TI>   `Good' Atmosphere Reported at Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Good' Atmosphere Reported at Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0706075194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0400 GMT 7 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0706075194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The economic talks in the Jordan--U.S.-Israeli 
forum will continue today. Our Washington correspondent Arye 
Golan reports that although the atmosphere in the talks is good 
and positive, no agreements have yet been reached. Israeli 
sources said that part of the talks -- pertaining to the 
demarcation of the road from Jordan to Egypt via Israel -- may 
be relocated to the region. Israel claims that the marking and 
measuring work could be used to demarcate the border between the 
two countries, an issue which Jordan would like to tackle 
already at this point. It was further reported that the United 
States may be involved in the paving of this road. 

</TEXT>

