<F P=100> Morocco </F>
<H3> <TI>   Filali To Reshuffle Cabinet; Opposition Not Included </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Filali To Reshuffle Cabinet; Opposition Not Included </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606132994 Rabat MAP in English 1237 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0606132994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rabat MAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Rabat, Jun. 06 (MAP) -- The newly-appointed Moroccan 
Premier Abdellatif Filali will partially reshuffle the present 
cabinet, 'AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT' daily Monday reported. Such a 
hypothesis is plausible, because Filali did not ask leaders of 
political parties to participate in the future government, 
during his consultations with these parties last week, the daily 
explained. 
  According to the daily, Filali expressed during the 
consultations some ideas on a government of national consensus, 
the consolidation of dialog between the government and the 
parliament and proposed a political and social truce to pave the 
way for a coming phase in which the opposition can participate 
in the government, the daily added. The newly-appointed premier 
confirmed to political parties that he will work for the 
consolidation of the role of the prime minister which means, 
according to 'AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT', that Filali will actually 
assume all his tasks as premier. Filali will propose the list 
of the new cabinet to King Hassan II next Wednesday, the daily 
said. 
  Leaders of opposition parties, namely those of the Istiqlal 
Party and the Socialist Union of Popular Forces had told the 
daily that they would not participate in the Filali government 
and expressed a reserved optimism as to the possibility to open 
up the channels of `a different dialog' between the government 
and the opposition. 
  The daily said that the opposition parties will present a 
joint memorandum to Filali expressing their viewpoint on the 
questions raised during the consultations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

