<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Leader Says Muslim Brotherhood Has No Structure </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Leader Says Muslim Brotherhood Has No Structure </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0606184794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1815 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0606184794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 6 Jun (MENA)--The northern al-Jizah 
Prosecution Office continued its interrogation of Muslim 
Brotherhood General Guide Hamid Abu-al-Nasr today. After four 
hours of questioning, the prosecution decided to resume the 
interrogations Thursday. 
  Abu-al-Nasr told his interrogators that the Muslim 
Brotherhood has had no official or structural organization since 
the decision to dissolve it in 1954. He said he is assuming the 
post of the group's general guide to shoulder his responsibility 
in filing lawsuits demanding that the dissolution decision be 
repealed. He noted that this is currently being examined by the 
judiciary. 
  Abu-al-Nasr said that as a general guide he issues 
statements 
expressing the Muslim Brotherhood's views on various issues. He 
stressed that he respects the Constitution and the laws and that 
he expresses his opinion through legitimate means allowed by law. 

</TEXT>

