<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Officers To Be Prosecuted for Selling Arms </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Police Officers To Be Prosecuted for Selling Arms </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0606181494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1710 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0606181494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 6 Jun (MENA)--Interior Minister Hasan al-Alfi 
has decided to refer four police officers to the Higher State 
Prosecution Office for interrogation for selling arms from the 
Interior Ministry arms depots. These officers are Major Samir 
Mahmud Mujahid, chief of the arms depot at the General 
Administration for Police Supply; Major Hani Sabri Mahmud, chief 
of the Returned Arms Department at the same administration; 
Major Mustafa 'Ashur, depots secretary at the Central Security 
Department; and Captain Iyhab Nafi', head of the Department of 
Returned Arms at the police supply. 
  The Interior Ministry statement released today said that the 
four officers sold five Lee Enfield rifles, three automatic 
rifles, and a quantity of rounds to certain arms and ammunition 
dealers. The investigating agencies continue their efforts to 
seize other quantities of arms and ammuntion that were sold with 
the knowledge of the four officers. 
  The interior minister earlier pensioned off the four 
officers 
as soon as their involvement in this operation was uncovered. 
It should be recalled that the interior minister issued 
directives for periodic inspection of the arms and ammunition 
depots to make sure that the regular instructions on the 
handling of various arms were implemented. 

</TEXT>

