<F P=100> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Explosion in Mazar-e Sharif Kills Militia Members </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Explosion in Mazar-e Sharif Kills Militia Members </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606172294 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 
GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0606172294 </F>
<F P=104>  Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Pashto </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Reports from reliable security sources say that last 
Saturday [4 June], a huge explosion took place in the Huzori 
Bagh, a five-story building in Mazar-e Sharif, in which at the 
present the so-called Central Office of Jenbish [National 
Islamic Movement of North, led by Dostam] is located. 
  As a result of this explosion a number of militiamen were 
killed and the building was damaged. 
  Eye-witnesses say that the number of such explosion has 
recently increased, which indicates chaos in the militias 
security systems. 

</TEXT>

