<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Awqaf Minister Values RCC Decree </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Awqaf Minister Values RCC Decree </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0606115694 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 2000 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0606115694 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dr. 'Abd-al-Mun'im Ahmad Salih, minister of awqaf 
and religious affairs, has valued the Revolution Command Council 
[RCC] Decree No. 59, issued on 4 June, stipulating the 
amputatation of the thief's right hand at the wrist. 
  The minister told INA's correspondent the decree is in line 
with God's Book and the provisions of the Islamic Law and in 
harmony with God's words: As to the thief, male or female: Cut 
off his or her hands, a punishment by way of example, from God, 
for their crime, and God is exalted in power. [Koranic verse] 
  The minister added that this legislation is appropriate to 
address the robbery cases noted in the decree and that the 
issuance of the decree is in line with the campaign of faith and 
jihad led by the faithful leader struggler President Saddam 
Husayn and to remedy the crimes of theft. 
  He noted that the rule of God is better than all other rules 
in achieving deterrence that immunizes society against crime. 
He asserted that the RCC decree is in implementation of God's 
rule. 
  But who, for a people whose faith is assured, can give 
better 
judgment than God? [Koranic verse] 

</TEXT>

