<H3> <TI>   Barzani, Islamic Movement Leader View Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Barzani, Islamic Movement Leader View Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0606185594 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0606185594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mas'ud Barzani, leader of the Kurdistan Democratic 
Party in Iraqi Kurdistan, met in Irbil today with Shaykh 'Uthman 
'Abd-al-'Aziz, leader of the Islamic Movement in Kurdistan. 
Barzani said that implementing a cease-fire in northern Iraq is 
not possible without 'Uthman's approval. 
  An Islamic Movement spokesman reported that the two leaders 
emphasized their united position on the current fighting in 
Iraqi Kurdistan. 
  The spokesman added that they also discussed the cease-fire 
in Irbil and the prospect of forming an executive committee, 
made up of representatives of the three warring parties in 
northern Iraq and the Iraqi National Congress, to implement a 
cease-fire in al-Sulaymaniyah. 

