<H3> <TI>   Al-Majali's Cabinet Reshuffle Overcoming Difficulties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Majali's Cabinet Reshuffle Overcoming Difficulties </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Ministers Resign </H4>

<F P=102> JN0706142394 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1400 GMT 7 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0706142394 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Jordanian News Agency has learned that the 
ministers tendered their resignations and placed them at the 
disposal of Prime Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali at noon 
today. 
  The agency also learned that Dr. al-Majali will introduce a 
reshuffle that includes a number of portfolios in his 
government, in which deputies [from the House of 
Representatives] may not take part at this stage. 
  The reshuffle is expected to be announced soon after a royal 
decree is issued. 

</TEXT>

