<H3> <TI>   Foreign Office Sets Up Separate Kashmir Directorate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Office Sets Up Separate Kashmir Directorate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0406080694 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 1500 
GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0406080694 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Urdu </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A separate Kashmir Directorate has been set up in 
the Foreign Office to highlight the Kashmir issue worldwide. A 
spokesman of the Pakistan People's Party [PPP] said in Islamabad 
that the step has been taken on the prime minister's directive. 
He said the prime minister would like to expose the brutal 
atrocities carried out by Indian forces in occupied Kashmir, 
adding that she attaches significant importance to the Kashmir 
issue whenever she pays a visit abroad. The PPP spokesman said 
the government after careful consideration has formulated a 
strategy to secure international support for its just stand on 
Kashmir. He expressed the hope that its efforts will get a 
considerable boost as a result of Ms. Bhutto's upcoming visits 
to the United States and Russia. 

</TEXT>

