<H3> <TI>   Sanaa Official: Southern Jets Attack Northern Forces </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sanaa Official: Southern Jets Attack Northern Forces </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0706083994 Paris AFP in English 0820 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0706083994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, June 7 (AFP) -- Southern Yemeni warplanes 
flying from Aden airport attacked northern forces all along the 
front line around the southern port city from daybreak Tuesday 
[7 June], Yemeni Planning Minister 'Abd-al-Karim al-Iryani said. 
  The planes were attacking northern positions from Little 
Aden, just west of the main city, to Lahij to the north, 
"continuously bombarding the whole front," he said. 
  "This is a violation of the ceasefire," announced by the 
Sanaa authorities late Monday, al-Iryani said. 
  The ceasefire took effect midnight Monday (2100 GMT) but 
collapsed six hours later. 
  Al-Iryani said the Sanaa government would inform UN 
Secretary-General Butrus Butrus-Ghali about the southern air 
raids "immediately." 
  Asked whether the northern forces were firing back, 
al-Iryani 
said "I presume so." 
  A correspondent in Aden said northern artillery was pounding 
the airport and surrounding area for the third straight day in 
an attempt to prevent it being used as a base for the warplanes. 

</TEXT>

