<H3> <TI>   UN Chief Comments on Resolution on Yemen Crisis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Chief Comments on Resolution on Yemen Crisis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0706074894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0607 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0706074894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 7 Jun (MENA) -- UN Secretary General Dr. 
Butrus Butrus-Ghali has expressed his hope that UN envoy to 
Yemen al-Akhdar Ibrahimi will succeed in convincing the Yemeni 
parties to implement the Security Council resolution on the 
Yemeni crisis. 
  In an interview with the Voice of Arabs Radio today, he 
described the Security Council resolution on the crisis in Yemen 
as a positive step. He emphasized that if each side insists on 
its stand, the issue may be put forth to the Security Council 
again for the necessary decisions. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

