<H3> <TI>   Radio Reports Japan's Support for Unity, Democracy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Radio Reports Japan's Support for Unity, Democracy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0606065794 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0606065794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Government of Japan has asserted its support 
for unity and democracy in the Yemeni Republic, regretting the 
exceptional situation our country is experiencing. 
  A press statement issued by the Press Office of the Japanese 
Foreign Ministry -- a copy of which was given to the Yemeni News 
Agency, SABA', by the Japanese Embassy -- said the Government of 
Japan welcomes the announcement of the government of the Yemeni 
Republic of its acceptance of Security Council Resolution 924, 
issued on 1 June, and its willingness to implement it. 
  The Government of Japan expressed its hope that all the 
parties concerned will respond to the Security Council 
resolution. 

</TEXT>

