<H3> <TI>   Qatari `Reservations' Over GCC Statement Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Qatari `Reservations' Over GCC Statement Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0606064594 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0606064594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by "a responsible source" at the Foreign Ministry </F>
of the State of Qatar] 
  [Text] The State of Qatar has voiced support for the 
Security Council Resolution No. 924 on the situation in the 
Yemeni Republic and its constant position on the need to end the 
fighting between the Yemeni brothers and resort to dialogue to 
solve the problem. The State of Qatar, however, has voiced 
reservations over two paragraphs of the statement issued 
yesterday, 5 June 1994, at the end of the session of the 
Ministerial Council of the Gulf Cooperation Council [GCC] on the 
situation in Yemen, because these two paragraphs do not refer to 
the legitimate name of the fraternal country, the Yemeni 
Republic, as mentioned in the Security Council resolution. In 
addition, the two paragraphs do not note the importance of 
preserving Yemen's unity that was set up by consent and public 
referendum. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

