<H3> <TI>   Al-Bid Reportedly To Resign When War Ends </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Bid Reportedly To Resign When War Ends </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0606120594 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1115 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0606120594 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] 'Ali Salim al-Bid, secretary general of the Yemeni 
Socialist Party, has announced that he will resign once the war 
in Yemen ends and that he will call for new elections. In a 
press interview published today, al-Bid noted that people should 
not be dragged into the conflict. He said that President 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih imposed on him a fait accompli after declaring 
war against the South on 27 April. Al-Bid added that he will 
never again take the hand of 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

