<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aden Radio Claims Sanaa Regime Facing `Last Hours' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aden Radio Claims Sanaa Regime Facing `Last Hours' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0606190394 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1500 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0606190394 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1500 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Presidential Council of the Democratic 
Republic of Yemen has issued a call to the sons of the Yemeni 
people, in which it pointed out that there was irrefutable 
evidence that 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih is the one who is issuing 
orders to his forces to carry out barbarous acts in peaceful 
towns and villages. [passage omitted] 
  The call confirmed that Aden and every inch of the territory 
of the Democratic Republic of Yemen, which he imagined in his 
sick dreams he would control, were beyond him. The call said 
that it was time to get rid of this bloody regime, whose hands 
had been smeared by blood since he took control of the northern 
governorates. It appealed to the sons of our Yemeni people to 
assume their patriotic duties to destroy this malignant microbe, 
which had corrupted many aspects of life in all parts of the 
coutnry. 
  The call confirmed that the Sanaa regime was approaching its 
end and was facing its last hours. It called on citizens to cut 
off supplies to its forces, because they had become tired and 
exhausted, and because the regime had failed to achieve its 
promises to them that they would be in Aden within two days. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

