<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Asnaj Calls For Isolating North's Officials </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Asnaj Calls For Isolating North's Officials </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0506094494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0915 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0506094494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 5 Jun (MENA) -- 'Abdallah al-Asnaj, who was 
recently appointed deputy prime minister and foreign minister in 
the Aden government, holds officials in Sanaa responsible for 
continuing the war and violating Security Council Resolution 
934, which stipulates an immediate cease-fire in Yemen. 
  In an exclusive statement to MENA, al-Asnaj called for 
isolating these officials regionally and internationally. He 
said: Giving them the feeling that there will be a decision to 
isolate them will make them accept the cease-fire 
unconditionally. 

</TEXT>

