<H3> <TI>   Al-Asnaj Urges Dispatch of International Observers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Asnaj Urges Dispatch of International Observers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0706073494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0610 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0706073494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 7 Jun (MENA) -- 'Abdallah al-Asnaj who has 
been appointed deputy prime minister and foreign minister in the 
Aden government has reiterated his country's commitment to 
implementing Security Council Resolution 924 on the crisis in 
Yemen. 
  In statements to Voice of the Arabs Radio today, he welcomed 
Sanaa's declaration of a cease-fire on all combat lines, noting 
the importance of a serious and actual commitment to the new 
date. He called for sending international observers to ensure 
that the cease- fire is not breached. 
  Al-Asnaj's statements are the first southern reaction to 
Sanaa's unilateral decision to cease fire as of midnight (?last 
night). 

</TEXT>

