<F P=102>   PM0606132694 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 4 Jun 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> PM0606132694 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by 'Abdallah Hammudah and Lutfi Shatarah: "Sanaa </F>
Appoints New Ambassador to Poland To Facilitate Conclusion of 
Arms Deals"] 
  [Excerpts] London -- The new Yemeni ambassador, Sharaf 
al-Sa'idi, who was an under secretary at the Foreign Ministry, 
Aden branch, arrived in the Polish capital, Warsaw yesterday to 
assume his duties there. Charge D'Affaires Muhammad Sharaf has 
been withdrawn because of his objection to an arms deal the 
Sanaa leadership had intended to conclude with the two companies 
Senzen and Sezbex [as transliterated] one month before the war 
broke out in Yemen. [passage omitted] 
  Well-informed sources say that the most important task 
assigned to him [the new ambassador] is to facilitate the 
Military Economic Establishment's task of concluding arms deals 
with Warsaw. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

