<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Knesset Committee Members Visit Northern Command </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Knesset Committee Members Visit Northern Command </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0606143794 Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ in Hebrew 6 Jun 94 p A4 </F>
<F P=103> TA0606143794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by military correspondent Eytan Rabin] </F>
  [Text] Members of the Knesset Foreign Affairs and Defense 
Committee headed by Knesset member [MK] Ori Or yesterday toured 
the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] Northern Command and south 
Lebanon. The committee members were briefed by senior Northern 
Command officers about the reasons for the Air Force attack on a 
Hizballah training camp in the Ba'labakk area. They were also 
briefed about possible terrorist attacks. 
  MK Or said that if Lebanon disarms Hizballah it will be 
possible to speak about evacuating the security zone. 
  Likud Chairman Binyamin Netanyahu expressed support for the 
IDF operation in Lebanon and voiced total support for the 
government's decisions in this regard. 
  Meanwhile the state of alert on the northern border 
continues. Senior military sources said despite the fact that no 
Katyushas have been fired by Hizballah since Friday they are 
continuing their activity in the security zone. 
  The sources say that the terrorists are trying to plant 
explosive charges, to attack outposts, and to kidnap soldiers. 
The terrorists are also trying to smuggle suicide squads into 
the security zone for attacks against IDF and SLA [South 
Lebanese Army] forces. 
  "We are convinced that Hizballah will try to carry out a 
spectacular attack in retaliation for the Air Force attack," 
said a senior Northern Command source. 
  Major General Yitzhaq Mordekhay, commander of the Northern 
Command, will today brief the General Staff about recent 
developments in Lebanon. 

</TEXT>

