<F P=100> IRAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Thai Envoy Handed Protest on Arrest of Nationals </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Thai Envoy Handed Protest on Arrest of Nationals </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0706095794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0330 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0706095794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yesterday afternoon the Thai ambassador in Tehran 
was summoned to the Foreign ministry and handed a note of 
protest by the deputy foreign minister and head of the 
Department for Southern and Eastern Affairs. The Central News 
Unit reports this note protested the arrest of several Iranians 
on the trumped-up charges of their attempting to blow up the 
Zionist regime's embassy in Bangkok and also to related 
interviews by Thai officials. 
  In this note of protest, the Islamic Republic of Iran has 
demanded an immediate response from the Thai Government and has 
asked for documented proof of the charges brought against the 
Iranian nationals. It has also asked the Thai Government to 
arrange a meeting between officials of the Islamic Republic's 
consulate in Bangkok and the accused. 

</TEXT>

