<F P=100> IRAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   * Nationals Seeking Employment Expelled From Cyprus </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    * Nationals Seeking Employment Expelled From Cyprus </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94LA0170B Tehran KEYHAN-E HAVA'I in Persian 4 May 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> 94LA0170B </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran KEYHAN-E HAVA'I </F>
<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

  [Text] Larnaca, 10 Ordibehesht [30 April] IRNA -- Last 
Wednesday the Cyprus Government expelled 30 Iranians, several of 
whom had just arrived at Larnaca Airport the same day. 
  One of the expelled Iranians, Reza Payami, said: The reason 
for expelling this group still has not been announced by the 
Cyprus police. 
  He said their expulsion was likely related to a theft that 
took place two weeks ago at a household appliances store. 
  Another of the individuals expelled said without giving his 
name: I was arrested by the Larnaca police as soon as I reached 
the airport. 
  He also claimed that the airport police tried in various 
ways 
to take the $1,800 he had away from him. 
  He said that he was forced to sell some of his household 
furnishings to make his trip to Cyprus possible. 
  A number of these expelled Iranians, citing deception or 
extortion of Iranians seeking work in Cyprus, asked Iran's 
embassies to cooperate with Iranians seeking work in various 
countries. 

</TEXT>

