<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Welcomes Yemeni Cease-Fire Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Welcomes Yemeni Cease-Fire Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606234794 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 2200 
GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0606234794 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Among its reactions, Algeria has welcomed with 
satisfaction the Yemeni Government's decision to accept the 
cease-fire beginning at midnight tonight. In a statement by the 
official spokesman of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Algeria 
welcomed the Yemeni Government's decision and expressed the hope 
that the Yemeni brothers would immediately begin a dialogue and 
lay the foundations of a just and permanent settlement to the 
conflict based on the protection of the Yemeni people's higher 
interests. 
  The statement added that Algeria, in the words of head of 
state Liamine Zeroual, had repeatedly warned the Yemeni brothers 
of the great risks of the conflict to Yemen. The head of state 
had insistently indicated the need for dialogue and consultation 
to prevail in the confrontation, especially when he received the 
two special Yemeni envoys and in the greetings message that he 
sent to the leaders of that country on the occasion of the 
Yemeni national day. 
  Within this context, Algeria renews its desire and readiness 
to offer its cooperation and that of the AMU [Arab Maghreb 
Union]--of which Algeria currently holds the presidency--with 
the aim of putting an end to this bloody struggle. 

</TEXT>

