<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iran's Velayati Meets With al-Asad, Hizballah's Nasrallah </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iran's Velayati Meets With al-Asad, Hizballah's Nasrallah </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0606142094 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 5 Jun 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> PM0606142094 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Salwa al-Ustuwani] </F>
  [Text] Damascus -- Syrian President Hafiz al-Asad has 
received a message from Iranian President 'Ali Akbar 
Hashemi-Rafsanjani stressing Iran's support for Syria in the 
event of any aggression on it following recent Israeli raids on 
Lebanon and the escalation in the military situation. 
  Iranian Foreign Minister 'Ali Akbar Velayati delivered the 
message to President al-Asad during their meeting in Damascus 
yesterday. The objective of his visit is to hold talks with 
senior Syrian officials on conditions in the region, especially 
the military deterioration in Lebanon and Israel's recent 
aggression on Hizballah's base in the Lebanese al-Biqa'. 
  Upon his arrival in the Iranian Embassy in Damascus Velayati 
met with a Hizballah delegation led by Secretary General Hasan 
Nasrallah. They discussed developments in the situation in 
Lebanon in the light of the continued Israeli attacks. Velayati 
stressed Iran's absolute support for the Lebanese resistance 
against the Israeli occupation. 
  Iranian sources in Damascus have told AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT that 
the Hizballah secretary general held talks with some senior 
Syrian officials on conditions and coordinating positions with 
Syria. 

</TEXT>

