<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Likely To `Return' to Gaza, Jericho in Jul </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Likely To `Return' to Gaza, Jericho in Jul </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0706095194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0903 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0706095194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, 7 Jun (MENA) -- Informed Palestinian sources 
have stated that PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat intends to return to 
Jericho and Gaza in July leading the Palestinian leadership and 
PLO institutions. 
  The sources stressed that a final and definitive date for 
'Arafat's return has not been set despite much talk about 
unrealistic dates. They say the return is likely to be in July 
so that it will precede the dates of municipal and legislative 
elections and they note that the elections, due for October, are 
inconceivable in the absence of 'Arafat and PLO institutions and 
agencies connected with the election campaign. 
  The sources said 'Arafat will return to Gaza and Jericho 
accompanied by 400 high-ranking leaders and agencies associated 
with the daily routine who have not been separated from 'Arafat 
for a quarter of a century. 

</TEXT>

