<H3> <TI>   King Husayn Chairs Part of Cabinet Session </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    King Husayn Chairs Part of Cabinet Session </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0406151294 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1400 GMT 4 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0406151294 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] His Majesty King Husayn chaired part of the 
cabinet's session at the Prime Ministry at noon today in the 
presence of His Highness Crown Prince Hasan, Prime Minister Dr. 
'Abd-al-Salam al- Majali, and Royal Hashemite Court Chief, His 
Excellency al-Sharif Zayd Bin-Shakir. 
  In a news conference following the session, His Majesty King 
Husayn said a review was made of both the regional situation and 
the expected developments in the coming phase. His majesty 
added that during the session there was emphasis on the need for 
this country to remain cohesive as one family from various 
origins and descents. He said we should enjoy awareness and 
affiliation, and that we should also study all that took place 
and has thus far taken place, so we will draw the conclusions 
required for effective action that guarantees the country's 
future in terms of its steadfastness, in order to serve the 
kinsfolk and brothers in Palestine with regard to their rights 
on their national soil. 

