<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   North Reported To Advance on Aden </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    North Reported To Advance on Aden </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0706110594 Paris AFP in English 1018 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0706110594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Aden, Yemen, June 7 (AFP) -- Northern Yemeni 
troops advanced closer to the south's bastion of Aden in a snap 
offensive on Tuesday [7 June] and four people died and more than 
40 were wounded in shelling as a ceasefire collapsed, 
correspondents reported. 
  Northern forces loyal to President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih 
captured the Sabr village 20 kilometers (12 miles) north of Aden 
in a push which took them several kilometres (miles) closer to 
the city, an AFP correspondent witnessed at the front line. 
  Southern Lieutenant Muhammad Husayn accused the Sanaa 
authorities of using the ceasefire, announced unilaterally by 
Salih's government late Monday, to mass troops and tanks in 
preparation for the dawn advance. 
  There were heavy artillery exchanges as southern forces 
tried 
to halt the northern tank offensive. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

