<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Talks With Russian Deputy Prime Minister Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Talks With Russian Deputy Prime Minister Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Agreement Reached To Increase Trade </H4>

<F P=102> BK0406080894 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 
GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0406080894 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] India and Russia have agreed to increase bilateral 
trade up to the 5,000-crore-rupee mark in the next two years. 
This view was expressed at a meeting of the cochairmen of the 
Indo- Russian Joint Commission, Mr. Pranab Mukherjee, and the 
deputy prime minister of Russia, Mr. Yuriy F. Yarov, in New 
Delhi today. Mr. Yarov assured India that Moscow will fully 
implement the agreement signed during President Yeltsin's visit 
to New Delhi. He said Russia will try to further rationalize 
import duties to facilitate speedy imports from India. The 
talks will continue till Tuesday. 

</TEXT>

