<H3> <TI>   Diplomat To Head UN Fact-Finding Mission to Yemen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Diplomat To Head UN Fact-Finding Mission to Yemen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0406143194 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 1200 
GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0406143194 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] [Announcer] The appointment of the Algerian 
diplomat Lakhdar Brahimi at the head of the UN fact-finding 
commission to Yemen has been received with great Yemeni and 
international satisfaction. Mr. Brahimi welcomes this mission 
to solve this fratricidal conflict. Over to you Abdelkader 
Djeridi. 
  [Djeridi] Mr. Lakhdar Brahimi, who was appointed the day 
before yesterday at the head of a UN mission to Yemen, said to 
MBC that he would begin the implementation of this mission 
immediately in accordance with UN resolution 924 issued last 
Thursday. 
  Mr. Brahimi, who has expressed his satisfaction with this 
mission and its acceptance by the parties in conflict, said that 
his mission was limited to fact-finding, getting acquainted with 
the situation existing in Yemen, and presenting a report on it 
to UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

