<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   National Transitional Council Elects 6 Deputy Chairmen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Transitional Council Elects 6 Deputy Chairmen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606203294 Algiers ENTV Television Network in Arabic 1900 
GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0606203294 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers ENTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Six deputy chairmen of the Transitional National 
Council were elected today in accordance with the internal 
statute passed a week ago. The Transitional National Council 
today held a session chaired by Mr. Abdelkader Bensalah, the 
council's chairman, to begin the election of six deputy chairmen 
from among the 22 candidates. Over to Nacema Kerat. 
  [Kerat] The election was held today by secret ballot and 
resulted in only two candidates winning in the first round by 
obtaining the majority required by the internal statute. They 
were Mr. Mohamed Taher (Dilmi), national secretary of the UGTA 
[Algerian General Workers Union], and Mr. Abdelmadjid 
(Monacera), national secretary in charge of information in HAMAS 
[Islamic Society Movement]. 
  This meant that a second round had to be held to elect the 
other four deputy chairmen. Following the voting in this round, 
the following were elected as deputy chairmen: Abdelouahab 
(Oughidmi) of the Sons of the Martyrs Organization, Abdelhafiz 
Amoukran (Elhaceni) of the War Veterans' Organization, Nacer 
(Sakhri) of the National Party for Solidarity and Development, 
and Hacen (Haider) of the National Union of Algerian Farmers. 
  Thus the council has completed the formation of its bureau 
that is composed of a chairman and six deputy chairman. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

