<F P=100> Inter-Arab Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   League Regrets New Outbreak of Yemeni Fighting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    League Regrets New Outbreak of Yemeni Fighting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0706150194 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1400 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0706150194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Arab League regrets the new eruption of fighting 
in Yemen only a few hours after Sanaa accepted a cease-fire as 
announced by its foreign minister, Muhammad Salim Basindwah. 
  Counselor Tal'at Hamid, the Arab League secretary general's 
press spokesman, said that the resumption of military action in 
Yemen does not help create the appropriate circumstances for 
negotiations. He added that the Arab League supports any Arab 
or international effort to stop this destructive war in line 
with UN Security Council Resolution 924. 
  Hamid reported that the Arab League secretary general is 
constantly in touch with Yemeni leaders in the north and south 
and with several other Arab countries to implement the Security 
Council resolution. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

