<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   IDF Soldiers Wound Five in Gaza Strip </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IDF Soldiers Wound Five in Gaza Strip </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0806075694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0400 GMT 8 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0806075694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Five Palestinians were wounded last night in Rafah 
by Israeli soldiers, who launched a search inside the autonomous 
area. A Qol Yisra'el reporter says the soldiers thought they 
were under fire, but the shooting was in fact from a Hamas 
[Islamic Resistance Movement] group that was firing in the air 
to celebrate the release of one of their members from the 
Qezi'ot prison. The Palestinian police are investigating the 
incident. 
  In Jericho, a Palestinian resident was lightly wounded 
yesterday when Palestinian police opened fire. The victim 
reportedly drove through a police roadblock without stopping. 
  In Gaza, the Palestinian police arrested four members of the 
Fatah Hawks for shooting and wounding six residents of the 
Tuffah neighborhood, one of them seriously and two others 
moderately. The Qol Yisra'el reporter says the Fatah Hawks 
tried to arrest a car thief, claiming they were from the 
Palestinian security service. The driver put up a fight and a 
shooting broke out. The four Hawks were arrested and their guns 
were confiscated. 
  In another incident, the Palestinian police demolished a 
house in the Rimal area that had been built illegally on public 
land. 
  An Israeli was lightly injured last night on the 
Trans-Samaria Highway when his car was stoned near the Arab 
village of Mashah. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

