<H3> <TI>   Security Officials Deny Report on Mosque Clash </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security Officials Deny Report on Mosque Clash </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0806065694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2150 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0806065694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 7 Jun (MENA) -- A responsible security 
official has denied a report by a news agency on a recent clash 
in the town of Akhmim in Suhaj Governorate between worshipers at 
al-Sahabah Mosque and a number of extremist elements. 
  The source said this report is totally false. There is no 
truth in it, since no confrontation or clashes of any kind took 
place at all, as the agency claimed. 
  According to the news agency report, six persons, including 
two extremists, were injured at al-Sahabah Mosque in Akhmim 
during a confrontation between worshipers and elements described 
as terrorist. 

</TEXT>

