<H3> <TI>   Peres on Charges of Omitted Excerpt in Holst Letter </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peres on Charges of Omitted Excerpt in Holst Letter </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0706193594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1900 GMT 7 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0706193594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Knesset Member [MK] Begin raised the suspicion that 
an excerpt has been omitted from Foreign Minister Peres' letter 
to Norwegian Foreign Minister Holst on the Jerusalem issue. MK 
Begin told Qol Yisra'el that the second clause in the letter 
does not follow from the first clause, and unless this is a mere 
stylistic defect, it is possible that a clause has been omitted. 
  Foreign Minister Peres reacted to this charge by saying that 
no clause has been omitted and the entire letter was published 
verbatim. Mr. Peres added that the Likud people realize that 
the letter does not harm Jerusalem's status in any way 
whatsoever, therefore they pick at it and raise false charges. 

</TEXT>

