<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Halakhic Edict Rules 'Arafat `Deserves to Die' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Halakhic Edict Rules 'Arafat `Deserves to Die' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0806111694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0900 GMT 8 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0806111694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Rabbi Shlomo Goren [former chief army chaplain] has 
once again published a halakhic edict pertaining to political 
affairs; this time with regard to PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat. 
In his halakhic edict, Rabbi Goren contends that Yasir 'Arafat 
deserves to die according to both Israeli and international law, 
because he has declared a jihad. Our correspondent Gil Litman 
reports that the halakhic ruling is included in a communique 
published by the Committee of Jewish rabbis in Judaea, Samaria, 
and the Gaza Strip. 

</TEXT>

