<H3> <TI>   Water Losses Said Possible From Border Adjustments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Water Losses Said Possible From Border Adjustments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0606044794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0400 GMT 6 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0606044794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The water commissioner has warned that the border 
adjustments demanded by Jordan in the 'Arava could lead to the 
loss of water sources vital to Israel. He told our 
correspondent Shula Schmerling that the reservoir of ground 
water in the 'Arava meets the consumption needs of the 
settlements in the area, which amount to approximately 40 
million cubic meters per year. The water commissioner clarified 
that at the Washington talks, Israel will demand that all the 
outstanding water problems with Jordan, including the question 
of the al-Yarmuk River, the Jordan River, and the 'Arava, be 
discussed as one package. 

</TEXT>

