<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Military Activity in Southern Lebanon </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of Military Activity in Southern Lebanon </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Israeli Shelling, Flights </H4>

<F P=102> NC0706171894 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1530 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0706171894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Israeli occupation forces have continued 
their acts of aggression in the south. From 1100 to around 1500 
today, Israeli artillery continuously shelled Kafra, Yatar, 
Haris, Zibqin, Majdal Zun, al-Mansurah, Buyut al-Sayyid, 
al-Hinniyah and the outskirts of al-Qulaylah. This was 
accompanied by heavy machine-gun bursts and continual 
overflights by Israeli warplanes. 
  A correspondent from the NATIONAL NEWS AGENCY reported that 
the villages of the western sector are now experiencing a state 
of economic, educational, and social paralysis as a result of 
the repeated Israeli aggression. 
  Meanwhile, resistance groups carried out a strong attack 
against enemy forces near al-Ahmadiyah in Western al-Biqa'. 
[passage omitted] 
  Hizballah Deputy Secretary General Shaykh Na'im Qasim 
stressed that the al-Ahmadiyah operation today is one in a 
series of attacks in the confrontation with the usurper Israeli 
enemy. 

</TEXT>

