<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Salih Telephone Conversation With Sector Commander Cited </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Salih Telephone Conversation With Sector Commander Cited </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0806131294 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 8 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM0806131294 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Text" of telephone conversation between President Salih </F>
and unidentified Tawr al-Bahah sector commander; place and date 
not given] 
  [Text] Salih: You are working like a tortoise, not 
mechanized units...the mission has to be accomplished quickly, 
because time is money...time is money...time is money. 
  Sector commander: We request a delay for a few hours, 
because the situation is a tortoise situation, and we are 
working to coordinate. 
  Salih: Accomplish the mission, there should be no stumbling 
blocks in your way...this is what is important, and do not 
listen to anything, because it is designed for the outside, not 
the inside. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

