<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Presidential Council Member al-Zandani Interviewed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Presidential Council Member al-Zandani Interviewed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0706191394 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0706191394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Qatari Television last night carried an interview 
with Shaykh 'Abd-al-Majid al-Zandani, member of the Presidential 
Council. In the interview al-Zandani expressed the Yemeni 
people's appreciation for the State of Qatar and the brotherly 
people who proved that they support the right, principles, and 
unity of Yemen. He said the Yemeni people will never forget this 
noble and fraternal position of our brothers in Qatar. 
  The brother Presidential Council member said that countries 
which respect their pledges and agreements, maintain their 
credibility, and are eager to preserve security and peace are 
the ones that supported Yemeni unity, and continue to adopt the 
same position. 
  On the allegations that what is going on in Yemen is a 
sectarian conflict, Shaykh al-Zandani explained that the Yemenis 
are one people with one religion, and that there are no sects in 
Yemen. He said our people lived under the brotherhood of Islam 
for more than 1,000 years and that colonialism was responsible 
for dividing the country. As for the sectarian or racial calls, 
they have been incited by the secessionists in the Socialist 
Party with the aim of dismantling the unity of the Yemeni people. 
  He said we consider these calls as having foreign political 
motives and that they are paid for in order to terminate unity, 
but the secessionists only reaped disappointment. Our Yemeni 
people and all their groups and governorates are standing 
against the clique that rebelled against our people and carried 
weapons in their faces to incite a rift. 
  On the Security Council resolution, he said the government 
appreciates the resolution and announced that it will deal with 
the resolution in a positive manner, and will cooperate with the 
international envoy and the fact-finding mission. He said we 
are satisfied because the Security Council resolution has 
tackled the problem as a united political entity that is the 
Republic of Yemen, and we hope that the United Nations will be 
able to understand what is going on in Yemen. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

