<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Secessionist' Elements Reportedly Arrest GPC Members </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Secessionist' Elements Reportedly Arrest GPC Members </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0806060594 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0330 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0806060594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement issued by "a responsible source" at the GPC </F>
General Committee] 
  [Text] The GPC's [General People's Congress] Standing 
Committee has learned that the security agencies affiliated with 
the gang of apostasy and secession in Aden have in the past few 
days made collective arrests of many leaders and members of the 
GPC branch in Aden, the economic and trade capital of the unity 
state, which is now controlled by the gang of those who rebelled 
against unity, democracy, and constitutional legitimacy, and 
threw them in jails. 
  Information confirms that the security agencies of the rebel 
gang raided houses of the GPC members on the pretext of 
searching for weapons before arresting them and taking them to 
detention centers. 
  Reliable sources said these security agencies did not inform 
the families of some GPC members that they were detained. Other 
information says the detainees were subjected to psychological 
and physical torture at the hands of experts in torture after 
they had refused to sign a statement supporting al-Bid's 
declaration of secession. 
  The GPC Standing Committee is astonished by this criminal 
conduct. It holds the criminal gang fully responsible for what 
may happen to the detainees at the hands of their henchmen and 
calls for their immediate release. The Standing Committee urges 
all political parties and organizations and the popular 
institutions and organizations to denounce this cowardly act, 
which was carried out by the elements of apostasy and secession 
in the Socialist Party. Having failed to face the valiant forces 
of unity and constitutional legitimacy, these elements seek to 
take revenge from the innocent civilians, including members of 
our organization. 
  We also draw attention to the fact that these criminal, 
suppressive acts carried out by the elements of rebellion and 
secession in the Socialist Party expose the rigid totalitarian 
mentality, the tyrannical suppressive will, and the 
conspiratorial policies that still live at the minds of the 
enemies of democracy, human rights, and civil liberties; and who 
do not respect other opinions. These acts are yet another 
addition to the series of crimes committed by this gang against 
our people and will not go unpunished. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

