<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Sanaa's Cease-Fire Violations, Battles </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Sanaa's Cease-Fire Violations, Battles </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0706190594 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in English 1600 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0706190594 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in English 1600 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An official source in the Democratic Republic of 
Yemen [DRY] affirmed that the Sanaa ruling regime and its head, 
'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, did not abide by the cease-fire as 
announced by it last night. The source indicated at 1130 last 
night information was picked up confirming that military 
reinforcements had come from Ta'izz to his forces and at 1216 
minutes [as heard] a call was picked up while ordering the Sanaa 
regime's forces in their first axis to advance on Aden. The 
source affirmed that there is a recording of the voice of 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih who was ordering his defense minister to 
continue the war. The order was carried out, but our forces 
repelled them and dealt killing blows to them. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

