<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aden `Minister': Plans for Counterattack `Being Made' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aden `Minister': Plans for Counterattack `Being Made' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0706164494 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1400 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0706164494 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1400 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Brother Muhsin Bin-Muhammad Bin-Farid, deputy 
prime minister and minister of planning and development, has 
said that defending the homeland is a life and death issue. He 
said that preparations were actively being made for a 
counterattack on the various fronts. In an interview for the 
Kuwaiti AL-SIYASAH, the minister stressed that the sons of the 
Democratic Republic of Yemen [DRY] were prepared and fully 
determined to regain all their territory and to drive out the 
aggressive invaders from the gang of the al-Ahmar clan. He said 
there were thousands of the sons of the Shabwah and Hadramawt 
Governorates who were going to the fronts and performing battle 
feats as part of their sacred duty to defend the homeland. They 
were fighting with high morale because they had a just cause. 
  He noted that the citizens had [word indistinct] well and 
had 
expressed their joy at the declaration of the establishment of 
the DRY as constituting a fundamental change in their political, 
economic, and social life and a strong factor for changing the 
political and military balance in south Yemen in general. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

