<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aden Radio Reports Shu'ayb Assault Repulsed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aden Radio Reports Shu'ayb Assault Repulsed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0706165094 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1400 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0706165094 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1400 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The popular resistance in Shu'ayb led by fighters of 
the liberation war with great courage and heroism repulsed 
yesterday the attacks of the gang of the al-Ahmar clan, 
inflicting on the enemy huge human and materiel losses. The 
popular resistance managed to kill a number of enemy officers 
and men of the invading forces. Among those killed was staff 
Colonel Muhammad 'Abdallah Haydar al-Sanhani, a relative of the 
leader of the gang of the al-Ahmar gang, who was [words 
indistinct] al-Hamzah and had been charged with leading the 
attack on Dhamar and the liquidation of al-Dali' and Shu'ayb. 
The popular resistance found in his possession orders from 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih charging him with the destruction of al-Dali' 
and Shu'ayb and killing their inhabitants without mercy, looting 
their possessions, and [word indistinct] their land, all of 
which is indicative of the savagery of the criminal and inhuman 
operations being conducted by the gang of the al-Ahmar clan and 
its (?hungry) retinue. 

</TEXT>

